snippet.textDisplay:
Loved the initial Zarsanga part The Queen of Pashtun Folklore, 
She is almost 75 years old, 
She belongs to a nomadic tribe called Kutanree (Kutan). 
She got no education so She cannot sing from a written paper. 
Most often she sings the songs that are composed and created by the common folk.
 Zarsanga has been to Germany, Belgium, Iraq, Dubai, America, France and UK and has enthralled thousands of Pakhtuns and local people with her voice. 
The famous musical numbers of Zarsanga, which she never misses at any musical event are "Da Bangriwal Pa Choli Ma Za (her first-ever song on radio)", 
"Zma Da Khro Jamo Yara",  Rasha Mama Zwi De",  "Zma Da Ghrono Pana Yara", and "Kht Me Zanzeri De"
